 a frequent visitor and lecturer in the prc platt is in a unique position to compare those early days of diplomatic contact to relations with the west today as china now emerges as a major player on the world stage and an economic power house nicholas platt long time china specialist three time us ambassador pakistan zambia and the philippines and author of the recently published memoir china boys will share his experiences and insights gained from a long and distinguished career in the diplomatic service and as president of the asia society in new york for 12 years as a young diplomatic officer in the early 1960s when china was firmly closed to the west platt took the unusual step of studying mandarin this put him in a key position when us relations to china suddenly opened platt was one of the state department officials chosen to accompany president nixon on his historic visit to china in 1972 the following year he and his family were stationed in beijing with the opening of a us liaison office the forerunner of the us embassy in the prc location philippines conference room encina hall 616 serra st 3rd floor stanford university stanford ca 94305 directions map fsi contact debbie warren parent research projects contemporary asia seminar series series topics china pakistan philippines zambia search aparc search within everything courses events fellowships news op eds people publications research other pages events of interest who's buying now south korean consumer nationalism before and after 1997 laura nelson the challenges and countermeasures for petrochina as china enters the wto and the relations between taiwan and china after accession to the wto luguang li wen jich patrick lin china and the world what does china expect from global economic and environmental governance wto g20 imf gmos and climate change in a broader perspective yves tiberghien china and the world interactions between china and other northeast asian countries workshop pdf+ support map & directi